openapi: 3.0.0 info: title: Numbers description: |- Service for getting, listing and managing virtual numbers. ## Authentication

Basic

Our basic security works with any project, use the client_id and client_secret that were displayed when you created your access key through the dashboard. Learn more about Sinch authentication and authorization
Security Scheme TypeHTTP
HTTP Authorization Schemebasic

OAuth

This is the recommended way to access our apis. Learn more about Sinch authentication and authorization
Security Scheme TypeOAuth2
clientCredentials OAuth FlowToken URL:
https://eu.auth.sinch.com/oauth2/token

Revoke URL:
https://eu.auth.sinch.com/oauth2/revoke
version: '1.0' paths: '/v1/projects/{projectId}/activeNumbers': get: summary: Lists virtual numbers for a project description: Lists all virtual numbers for a project. Learn about [authentication](#active-number). operationId: NumberService_ListActiveNumbers responses: '200': description: A successful response. content: application/json: schema: $ref: '#/components/schemas/v1ListActiveNumbersResponse' '400': description: 'If the page_token, number_pattern or order_by is not valid' content: application/json: schema: {} examples: response: value: error: code: 400 message: '' status: INVALID_ARGUMENT details: - type: BadRequest fieldViolations: - field: order_by description: Invalid order_by XXX parameters: - name: projectId description: Your project id can be found if you log into your account on dashboard.sinch.com. in: path required: true schema: type: string - name: regionCode description: 'Region code to filter by. ISO 3166-1 alpha-2 country code of the phone number. Example US, GB or SE.' in: query required: false schema: type: string - name: pattern description: Sequence of digits to search for. in: query required: false schema: type: string - name: searchPattern description: |- Search pattern to apply. - SEARCH_PATTERN_UNSPECIFIED: Null value - START: Numbers that start with the provided sequence of digits - CONTAINS: Numbers that contain the sequence of digits - END: Numbers that end with the sequence of digits in: query required: false schema: type: string enum: - SEARCH_PATTERN_UNSPECIFIED - START - CONTAINS - END default: SEARCH_PATTERN_UNSPECIFIED - name: type description: |- Number type to filter by. MOBILE, LOCAL or TOLL_FREE. - MOBILE: Numbers that belong to a specific range - LOCAL: Numbers that are assigned to a specific geographic region - TOLL_FREE: Number that are free of charge for the calling party but billed for all arriving calls in: query required: false schema: type: string enum: - MOBILE - LOCAL - TOLL_FREE default: MOBILE - name: capability description: |- Number capability to filter by. SMS and/or VOICE. - SMS: The SMS product can use the number - VOICE: The Voice product can use the number in: query required: false schema: type: string enum: - SMS - VOICE default: SMS - name: pageSize description: The maximum number of items to return. in: query required: false schema: type: integer format: int32 - name: pageToken description: 'The next_page_token value returned from a previous List request, if any.' in: query required: false schema: type: string - name: orderBy description: |- Supported fields for ordering by: number or display_name. https://cloud.google.com/apis/design/design_patterns#sorting_order. in: query required: false schema: type: string tags: - Active Number '/v1/projects/{projectId}/activeNumbers/{phoneNumber}': patch: summary: Update virtual phone number. description: |- With update virtual phone number you can move a number between different SMS services and give it a new friendly name. The phone number in e.164 format with leading +. Example +12025550134. in: path required: true schema: type: string requestBody: content: application/json: schema: $ref: '#/components/schemas/v1ActiveNumber' description: The number body to be updated required: true tags: - Active Number get: summary: Get a virtual number. operationId: NumberService_GetActiveNumber responses: '200': description: A successful response. content: application/json: schema: $ref: '#/components/schemas/v1ActiveNumber' '404': description: The active number could not be found content: application/json: schema: {} examples: response: value: error: code: 404 message: '' status: NOT_FOUND details: - type: ResourceInfo resourceType: sinch.unifiednumber.v1alpha2.ActiveNumber resourceName: '+12025550134' owner: '' description: '' parameters: - name: projectId description: Your project id can be found if you log into your account on dashboard.sinch.com. in: path required: true schema: type: string - name: phoneNumber description: The id of the active number to retrieve. in: path required: true schema: type: string tags: - Active Number '/v1/projects/{projectId}/activeNumbers/{phoneNumber}:release': post: summary: Release a virtual number from the project. description: Cancel your subscription for a specific virtual phone number. operationId: NumberService_ReleaseNumber responses: '200': description: A successful response. content: application/json: schema: $ref: '#/components/schemas/v1ActiveNumber' '404': description: The active number could not be found content: application/json: schema: {} examples: response: value: error: code: 404 message: '' status: NOT_FOUND details: - type: ResourceInfo resourceType: sinch.unifiednumber.v1alpha2.ActiveNumber resourceName: '+12025550134' owner: '' description: '' parameters: - name: projectId description: The ID of the project resource. Your project id can be found if you login to your account on dashboard.sinch.com. in: path required: true schema: type: string - name: phoneNumber description: The active phone number to release. in: path required: true schema: type: string tags: - Active Number '/v1/projects/{projectId}/availableNumbers': get: summary: Search virtual numbers description: Search for virtual numbers that are available for you to activate.
